Ad Text:
ISM Software Integration Lead

Executive Level 1

Melbourne 

Position overview

The occupant of this position is a member of the Operational Technology and Engineering (OTE) Section. The role of the OTE Section is to ensure the development, delivery and operation of measurement equipment and systems meet the Bureau's performance and functional requirements. This includes the following sensors/networks:

Radar and Wind Profilers
Automatic Weather Stations
Solar Radiation
Upper Air
Flood Warning
Sea Level

Operational Technology and Engineering bring together a diverse group of specialists and engineers who develop and support advanced engineering and technology solutions. The team delivers critical technical support across a broad suite of systems—including radars, rainfall stations, drifting buoys, dedicated observation platforms, satellites, and ship‑based technologies—to enable the organisation to meet its operational and business needs.

This position focuses on the activities to support the Bureau's current and future network of Automatic Weather Stations, particularly the software, testing, configuration and rollout aspects of these systems.

To succeed in this role, you will have:

Experience in software with mandatory scripting development, equipment testing, verification and operationalising and the ability to communicate these outcomes through written procedures/reports, and presentations.
Proven ability to lead within a team environment, to work with people, and encourage delivery and innovation.
Extensive experience in data acquisition, measurement technologies and engineering.
Extensive experience in mentoring and guiding technical teams.
Strong communication and liaison skills.
High level coordination and reporting skills.
Demonstrated experience in understanding, developing and implementing successful strategic initiatives.
Enthusiasm and drive. 

Application Closing Time and Date: 11:30pm, Friday 6 March 2026

For further information please review the position description on https://bomcareers.nga.net.au/?jati=AC85DCBD-22DA-79B6-5208-ECAAFABB0F13

Reapit – Who are we?

Reapit is the original, end-to-end business technology provider for estate agencies of all sizes. We’ve been helping sales and lettings agents to build relationships and grow their businesses for more than 25 years. Our technology connects property professionals in Europe, the Middle East, Australia, and New Zealand with buyers, sellers, tenants and landlords to power the relationships that change lives.


In Australia, Reapit stands as the preferred technology choice among the nation's leading estate agents and agencies. Tailored to the unique demands of the Australian property market, Reapit provides successful leaders with unparalleled tools across sales, property management, client relations, and data analytics, reinforcing their position at the pinnacle of real estate excellence.

What you’ll be doing

Reporting to the Global Head of Data you’ll be involved in the following;

Agentic Platform Development

Design and build scalable AI agent architecture to support autonomous task execution and workflow automation

Develop self-learning systems that adapt and improve performance based on customer transaction patterns and user interactions

Implement robust patterns and practices for multi-agent and AI augmented RPA workflows

Ensure security with customer data isolation and regulatory compliance

AI Powered Automation & Insights

Create intelligent systems for customer data analysis, market trend identification, and anomaly detection

Build automated workflows for lead qualification, maintenance management and many other agency tasks

Platform Engineering and Integration

Architect and maintain production-ready AI services using TypeScript/JavaScript, .NET, and/or Python on AWS infrastructure & services

Integrate AI capabilities with existing Reapit systems and third-party APIs while ensuring data consistency, performance and cost efficiency.

Implement monitoring, logging, and observability solutions for AI model performance and agent behaviour tracking

Technical Leadership and Innovation

Evaluate and integrate cutting-edge AI platforms, frameworks, and tooling to maintain competitive advantage

Collaborate with product and engineering teams to translate business requirements into technical AI solutions

Mentor wider engineers and establish best practices for AI development, testing, and deployment

Who we're looking for

At Reapit, we prioritise hiring individuals who share our values and possess the right attitudes and behaviours for success. Whilst some of the listed requirements may be important, don’t worry if you don’t meet all of them, we’d still like to hear from you.

5+ years of software engineering experience with strong proficiency in TypeScript/JavaScript, .NET, and/or Python

3+ years of hands-on experience building and deploying AI/ML systems for enterprise-grade solutions, preferably in a SaaS or platform environment.

Deep expertise with major AI platforms and frameworks (OpenAI, Anthropic, LangChain, TensorFlow, PyTorch)

Proven experience with AWS services including Lambda, ECS/EKS, S3, CloudFormation

Strong database skills with MySQL and experience with data pipeline development

Experience building autonomous agents, multi-agent systems, or intelligent workflow automation, as well as traditional RPA

Solid understanding of software architecture patterns, API design, and system integration principles

Bachelor's degree in computer science, AI/ML, or related technical field

Relevant AWS Certification in core or speciality paths

Knowledge of natural language processing, computer vision, or recommendation systems

Familiarity with MLOps practices, evaluation, and A/B testing frameworks

Experience with microservices architecture and event-driven systems

Understanding of data privacy regulations and security best practices for AI systems

Contributions to open-source projects in relevant domains

What your impact and success looks like

We expect your success and impact in the early stages of your career with us to look something like this:

Within 1 month:
You’ll be discovering how to, and actively integrate AI functionality into simple features in our products

Participating with the wider team, determining AI strategy and tooling

Within 3 months:

You will feel comfortable with the basics of the domain and Reapit’s products & services.

You will be able to demonstrate an understanding of the core areas of the technology stack.

You will be independently contributing new ideas to product and processes.

You will be contributing more advanced agentic features to Reapit products, and helping hone AI strategy from initial feature feedback

Within 6 months:


You will be able to work independently due to your continually growing understanding of our products and solutions.

Your contributions will be helping to shape the backlog and future direction of the wider products, where AI exists at its core

You’ll be an advocate for the AI strategy throughout the business, guiding the wider teams adoption

Don't tick all the boxes? Neither do we

We care about our industry and want it to become a more inclusive and diverse place to work. So, we’re driven by hiring not only by experience and relevance for the role but by sharing our values and the right attitudes and behaviours for success. We are committed to Equal Employment Opportunity through attracting and retaining a complementary team of employees and building an inclusive environment for all. We feel we have an empowering environment where everyone is supported and respected, and we want you to feel this too. We welcome new ideas, thinking and approaches, whilst listening to all
our employees.

“We are a 2025 Circle Back Initiative Employer – we commit to respond to every applicant.”

Our client is seeking a Senior AI Engineer to join a team of engineers building a platform that enables product teams to embed Generative AI into their solutions safely and effectively.

This role requires a strong software engineering background, combined with proven leadership skills to ensure delivery of secure, scalable, and ethical AI capabilities.

Key Responsibilities

Lead the design, development, and operation of cloud-native platform services, including AI-enabled components.
Collaborate with Product, Data, Architecture, and Compliance to deliver scalable, AI-capable software solutions.
Build reusable and composable software components that integrate AI capabilities for cross-team use.
Drive engineering best practices and operational excellence in production systems.
What We’re Looking For

5+ years of software engineering experience.
Strong expertise in modern software development practices and cloud-native distributed systems (AWS preferred).
Experience delivering complex, scalable software solutions, ideally with AI/ML integration.
Familiarity with AI/ML tools and frameworks (e.g., LLMs, RAG pipelines, LangChain, Hugging Face) is a plus.
Proven ability to foster a high-performance engineering culture

$10.00 - $20.00

Permanent - Full Time

Sydney (Head Office)

Who we are…

Founded in 2002, ELMO Software is the trusted provider of HR technology solutions to 2,000+ mid-sized organisations and more than one million end users across Australia and New Zealand.With a comprehensive suite of ISO-certified solutions that span the full employee lifecycle, ELMO Software is designed to scale as organisations grow. Flexible and configurable, ELMO’s one-stop HRIS fits to your specific needs and workflows.Through powerful technology, automation, data and analytics, ELMO Software empowers HR professionals to play an integral role in company decision making.

Life & Culture...

At ELMO you will be joining an epic team with the opportunity to make a big impact. We foster an authentic, collaborative, fun working environment and being an ELMOnian means you're part of an amazing team that will push you to grow, support you with challenges and allow you to shine. Some of our benefits include:

Paid Parental leave - 12 weeks primary, 6 weeks secondary
Birthday leave, YOU day each year, as well as connecting people leave (up to 6 weeks working from anywhere)
Inhouse Learning and Development initiatives

Our values:

Reimagine What's Possible - We believe innovation is human at its core. By staying open, fearless, and adaptive, we continuously push boundaries - while keeping people at the heart of everything we do.
Obsess over Customers – Everything we do is designed to positively impact our customers.
Help Others Thrive - Be they colleagues, communities or customers, we champion ways to help others thrive.
Be Fearlessly Optimistic - We bring unwavering positivity to any challenge, as we know it will drive meaningful change.

Please note: Our internal Talent Acquisition team has got this covered, we’re not open to using an agency for this role.

As our Lead AI Engineer, you'll spearhead the development of cutting-edge agentic AI solutions that automate complex HR processes, enhance employee experiences, and deliver unprecedented business intelligence.

This isn't just another AI engineering role; it's an opportunity to pioneer intelligent automation in HR technology while leading a world-class team.

Responsibilities:

Lead AI Architecture: Design and implement enterprise-scale AI systems
Build Agentic AI Solutions: Create intelligent agents that automate tasks
Drive Innovation: Create innovative solutions through the use of AI
Scale Intelligence: Transform our existing automation platform with advanced AI capabilities

Revolutionary AI Development:

Design and deploy agentic AI workflows that autonomously handle complex HR scenarios
Build intelligent automation agents using Large Language Models, RAG architectures, and multi-agent systems
Create real-time AI processing pipelines that enhance every aspect of the employee experience
Develop AI-powered integrations with 50+ SaaS platforms through our existing automation infrastructure

Technical Leadership:

Lead a growing AI team of ML/AI engineers and automation specialists
Mentor and develop junior engineers while building ELMO's AI centre of excellence
Drive technical decisions that will shape ELMO's AI strategy for years to come

Platform Innovation:

Integrate AI capabilities into our existing automation platform
Build scalable ML infrastructure on existing cloud infrastructure using the latest AI/ML services
Implement responsible AI practices ensuring privacy, fairness, and compliance with global regulations
Design APIs and SDKs that enable customers to build their own AI-enhanced workflows

Core AI/ML Expertise:

7+ years software engineering with 5+ years in AI/ML systems
3+ years leading technical teams (hiring, mentoring, performance management)
Deep hands-on experience with Large Language Models (OpenAI, Anthropic, AWS Bedrock)
Production deployment of 2+ generative AI applications
Strong knowledge of RAG architectures, vector databases, embedding models
Experience with agentic frameworks (LangChain, LlamaIndex, AutoGen, CrewAI)

Technical Leadership Skills:

Track record architecting complex AI projects from concept to production
Expertise in MLOps: model versioning, A/B testing, monitoring, retraining
Advanced Python with modern ML frameworks (PyTorch/TensorFlow)
Cloud ML platform experience (AWS SageMaker strongly preferred)
Understanding of enterprise SaaS, APIs, microservices, integration patterns
Experience with CI/CD, containerization, infrastructure as code

Leadership Qualities:

Team builder: Experience hiring, mentoring, and developing AI/ML talent
Communicator: Ability to translate complex AI concepts for business stakeholders
Innovator: Track record of identifying and implementing emerging AI technologies
Results-driven: Focus on measurable business outcomes and customer impact

Job Title: AI Platform Engineer -Agentic AI Development (Python, AWS)
Ad Text:
About Synechron:
Synechron is a global technology consulting firm that helps leading organizations accelerate digital transformation through innovation, expertise and agility. With more than 16,500 professionals across around 60 offices in 20 countries, we combine deep industry knowledge with advanced capabilities in such areas as AI, cloud, cybersecurity, and data engineering.
Our regional teams, supported by strategic delivery centers, provide scalable, cost-efficient solutions tailored to local markets. Through our award-winning Synechron FinLabs accelerators and strategic partnerships with AWS, Microsoft, Databricks, Salesforce, and ServiceNow, we enable clients to innovate fast and lead with confidence. For more information on the company, please visit our website or LinkedIn community.


Position Overview
Synechron Sydney is seeking an AI Platform Engineer to design and deploy agentic AI applications within the organizations environment. The ideal candidate will have strong knowledge of agentic AI frameworks, guardrails, token limitations, and AI application lifecycle management. While prior production-ready AI deployment experience is not mandatory, the candidate must demonstrate a solid understanding of how AI applications work and be able to integrate them into enterprise-grade platforms.
Key Responsibilities

Agentic AI Development

Build and prototype agentic AI applications using Python.

Implement frameworks for autonomous agents, orchestration, and decision-making.

Apply guardrails to ensure safe, ethical, and compliant AI behavior.

Platform Deployment

Deploy AI applications in organization's environment.

Leverage AWS services (Lambda, S3, EC2, SageMaker, DynamoDB, CloudFormation) for scalable deployment.

AI Application Lifecycle

Manage token limitations, context windows, and prompt optimization.

Integrate monitoring and logging for AI agent performance.

Collaboration

Work closely with architects, data scientists, and engineering teams.

Provide technical guidance on AI frameworks and deployment strategies.

Innovation

Explore emerging agentic AI frameworks and tools.

Contribute to best practices for AI application design and governance.

Required Skills & Experience

Strong programming skills in Python with AI/ML libraries (LangChain, LlamaIndex, Hugging Face).

Understanding of agentic AI frameworks, guardrails, and token management.

Experience deploying applications on AWS cloud (Lambda, SageMaker, EC2, S3, DynamoDB).

Familiarity with microservices architecture, APIs, and containerization (Docker/Kubernetes).

Knowledge of AI safety, compliance, and governance principles.

Excellent problem-solving and communication skills.

Synechron Sydney is seeking a Data Engineering Lead with strong expertise in data streaming, AWS EMR, and PySpark to support large-scale data migration and transformation initiatives. The ideal candidate will have hands-on experience building scalable data pipelines, migrating workloads to cloud platforms, and enabling advanced analytics for enterprise clients.

Key Responsibilities

Data Engineering & Pipeline Development

Design, build, and optimize data pipelines using PySpark and AWS EMR.

Implement real-time data streaming solutions with tools such as Kafka, Kinesis, or Spark Streaming.

Develop ETL/ELT workflows for structured and unstructured data.

Cloud Migration

Lead and support data migration projects from on-premise to AWS cloud.

Ensure data integrity, security, and compliance during migration.

Platform Engineering

Deploy and manage big data workloads on AWS EMR, S3, Redshift, DynamoDB, and Glue.

Collaboration

Work closely with architects, data scientists, and business stakeholders.

Required Skills & Experience

8+ years of experience in data engineering with strong migration project exposure.

Hands-on expertise in PySpark, AWS EMR, and big data frameworks.

Experience with data streaming technologies (Kafka, Kinesis, Spark Streaming).

Strong knowledge of AWS services (S3, Glue, Redshift, DynamoDB, Lambda).

Proficiency in SQL/NoSQL databases and data modeling.

Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines, Docker, Kubernetes for data workloads.

Strong problem-solving and communication skills.

Preferred Qualifications

AWS certification (Data Analytics Specialty, Solutions Architect).

Experience in BFSI or enterprise-scale migration projects.

Exposure to event-driven architectures and real-time analytics.

Knowledge of data governance, lineage, and compliance frameworks.

Why Synechron Sydney?

Opportunity to work on mission-critical data migration and streaming projects.

Collaborative, innovative, and client-focused work culture.

Competitive compensation and career growth opportunities.
